# Linux Automation Toolkit

This repository contains practical Bash scripts designed to automate real-world Linux system tasks.

## Features
- Automated backups
- System monitoring
- File cleanup
- Basic deployment automation

## Tech Stack
- Linux (Ubuntu)
- Bash scripting

## How to Use
1. Clone the repo
2. Navigate to scripts folder
3. Make scripts executable:
   chmod +x *.sh
4. Run scripts:
   ./backup.sh

## Why this project?
This project demonstrates hands-on experience with Linux automation, cron jobs, and system-level scripting.

